<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Grid Music</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<style>
body{
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  margin: 0;
  background-color: #282c34;
  color: #61dafb;
  font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
}

#grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(8, 1fr);
  gap: 10px;
  margin-top: 20px;
}

.grid-item {
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  border: 1px solid #61dafb;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
}

.grid-item.active {
  background-color: #bada55 !important;
}

/* Different colors for notes */
.note-C { background-color: #FFD700; }
.note-D { background-color: #FFA500; }
.note-E { background-color: #FF6347; }
.note-F { background-color: #8A2BE2; }
.note-G { background-color: #00CED1; }
.note-A { background-color: #3CB371; }
.note-B { background-color: #9370DB; }
.note-C2 { background-color: #FFD700; } /* higher octave C */

button {
  margin-top: 20px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #282c34;
  background-color: #61dafb;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;
}

button:hover {
  background-color: #282c34;
  color: #61dafb;
}

label {
  margin-top: 20px;
  font-size: 16px;
}

input {
  margin-top: 10px;
  width: 300px;
  -webkit-appearance: none;
  appearance: none;
  height: 10px;
  background: #61dafb;
  outline: none;
  opacity: 0.7;
  -webkit-transition: .2s;
  transition: opacity .2s;
  border-radius: 5px;
}

input:hover {
  opacity: 1;
}

span {
  margin-left: 5px;
  font-size: 14px;
}

/* Add this to your existing CSS styles */

#scale-selector {
font-size: 16px;
padding: 10px;
border: 2px solid #61dafb;
border-radius: 5px;
background-color: #282c34;
color: #61dafb;
outline: none;
}

#scale-selector:hover {
border-color: #282c34;
background-color: #61dafb;
color: #282c34;
}
p {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: black;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
}

h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: black;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;

}
</style>
<body>
<h2>Minor Scale</h2>
<p>The minor scale is a musical scale that, like the major scale, consists of seven notes. However, it has a different pattern of intervals, giving it a distinct sound that is often described as more melancholic or somber. The most common form of the minor scale is the natural minor scale, and its pattern of intervals is:
</p>
<p>
Whole - Half - Whole - Whole - Half - Whole - Whole
</p>
<p>
Lets illustrate this with the A natural minor scale:
</p>
<p>
A - B - C - D - E - F - G - A
</p>
<p>
Starting from A, you move up by a whole step to B, a half step to C, a whole step to D, another whole step to E, a half step to F, a whole step to G, and finally a whole step to return to A.
</p>
<p>
The natural minor scale is characterized by its minor third (the distance between the first and third notes) and minor seventh (the distance between the first and seventh notes). These intervals contribute to the scale's more subdued and introspective quality compared to the major scale.
</p>
<div data-controller="minorscale">
 <section id="instructions">
  <select id="scale-selector">
    <option value="C">C Minor Scale</option>
    <option value="D">D Minor Scale</option>
    <option value="E">E Minor Scale</option>
    <option value="F">F Minor Scale</option>
    <option value="G">G Minor Scale</option>
    <option value="A">A Minor Scale</option>
    <option value="B">B Minor Scale</option>
  </select>
</section>

  <div id="grid-container"></div>
  <button id="play-btn">Play</button>
  <button id="stop-btn">Stop</button>
  <label for="bpm-slider">BPM:</label>
  <input type="range" id="bpm-slider" min="60" max="200" value="120">
  <span id="bpm-value">120 BPM</span>
</div>
</div>
</body>
